Since Mark completed the first test in 8 hours, he had 8 - 5 = 3 hours left to complete the second test. The total number of questions on the first test is 75. We know that Mark completed 5 questions per hour, so the total number of questions on the first test is \text{Total questions on the first test} = 75 \times 5 = 375 \text{ questions} 
Since Mark had 3 hours to complete the second test, we can calculate the total number of questions on the second test as \text{Total questions on the second test} = 100 \times 5 = 500 \text{ questions} 
To find the number of questions Mark left incomplete, we subtract the total questions on the second test from the total questions on the first test \text{Incomplete questions} = 375 - 500 = -125 \text{ questions} 
Since Mark cannot have a negative number of questions, we must conclude that he completed all 500 questions on the second test. Therefore, the answer is -125.
The answer is: -125iteditoriala2022iteditoriala2022iteditoriala2022

