 First, we know that Hallie had dance practice for 1 hour on Tuesdays and 2 hours on Thursdays. Since she had dance practice on Saturdays twice as long as Tuesday's night class, we can represent her total dance practice time as 2 hours (Tuesday) + 1 hour (Thursday) + 2 hours (Saturday). This adds up to 5 hours in total. To find the number of hours she had dance practice per week, we divide the total hours by 7 (since there are 7 days in a week). 
 \text{Hours per week} = \frac{5}{7} 
 \text{Hours per week} = \frac{1}{7} \times 7 
 \text{Hours per week} = \frac{1}{7} \times 1 \text{ hour} 
 \text{Hours per week} = \frac{1}{7} \text{ hour} 
Therefore, Hallie had dance practice 1/7 of a week.
The answer is: 1/7enceenceence

 First, we need to find out how far Cho hiked in 8 hours at 14 kilometers per hour. This is calculated as follows \text{Distance} = \text{Speed} \times \text{Time} 
 \text{Distance} = 14 \text{ km/h} \times 8 \text{ h} 
 \text{Distance} = 112 \text{ km} 
Since Chloe stopped after 5 hours, we don't need to calculate her distance. Now, we need to find out how far Cho hiked in 3 hours at 9 kilometers per hour. This is calculated as follows \text{Additional distance} = \text{Speed} \times \text{Time} 
 \text{Additional distance} = 9 \text{ km/h} \times 3 \text{ h} 
 \text{Additional distance} = 27 \text{ km} 
To find the distance Cho hiked after stopping, we add the additional distance to the total distance \text{Final distance} = 112 \text{ km} + 27 \text{ km} 
