Since we already know that Naruto can lift a mountain 10 times higher than Kagiyami can, and we also know that Saskay can lift a mountain 12 times higher than Pompei can, we can set up a system of equations
 10:4 = \frac{P}{S} 

 10:12 = \frac{N}{K} 

Solving for K in the first equation gives us
 K = \frac{10P}{4S} 

 Solving for S in the second equation gives us
 S = \frac{10N}{12} 

Now, substitute S in the first equation to get
 K = \frac{10 \times \frac{10P}{4S}}{4} 

 K = \frac{10P}{4} 

